  <bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="index" id="bm_id3147143"><bookmark_value>mobile devices filters</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>pocket device appliances;$[officename] documents</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>$[officename] documents;mobile devices filters</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>Palm file filters</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>Pocket PC file filters</bookmark_value></bookmark><paragraph id="hd_id3147143" role="heading" level="1" oldref="33" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US"><variable id="mobiledevicefilters"><link href="text/shared/guide/mobiledevicefilters.xhp" name="Mobile Devices Filters for Pocket Device Appliances">Mobile Devices Filters for Pocket Device Appliances</link></variable></paragraph>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3143267" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="1">You can save and open $[officename] documents to and from several mobile devices file formats. Install the filters in the $[officename] Setup program. </paragraph>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3146957" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="2">Currently the following filters are available:</paragraph>
  <list type="unordered">
   <listitem>
    <paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3154823" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="3">AportisDoc for Palm OS compatible devices</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147209" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="4">Pocket Excel for Pocket PC compatible devices</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3166460" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="5">Pocket Word for Pocket PC compatible devices</paragraph>
   </listitem>
  </list>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3147653" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="6">Installing the Pocket PC filters under Windows will also install a DLL file that supports the synchronize software of your Pocket PC.</paragraph>
  <paragraph role="note" id="par_id3153252" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="7">The Java Runtime Environment is required to use the mobile device filters.</paragraph>
  <paragraph role="heading" level="2" id="hd_id3153665" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="8">Installing the mobile devices filters</paragraph>
  <list type="ordered">
   <listitem>
    <paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3148685" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="9">Close $[officename] and the Quickstarter.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3156023" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="10">If you have installed ActiceSync under Windows, disconnect your Pocket PC device from ActiveSync.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3153061" l10n="U" oldref="11">Start the <emph>$[officename] Setup</emph> program. There is a link to start Setup in your $[officepath] folder.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="12" role="listitem" id="par_id3146794" l10n="U">In Setup, choose the <emph>Modify</emph> option and click <emph>Next</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="13" role="listitem" id="par_id3151054" l10n="U">Open the <emph>Optional Components</emph> entry, then open the <emph>Mobile Device Filters</emph> entry. If an entry has a solid color it is already installed. If it has another color, click it until it shows a solid color.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="14" role="listitem" id="par_id3154138" l10n="U">Click <emph>Modify</emph>, answer any other dialogs, and end the Setup program with <emph>Complete</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
  </list>
  <paragraph role="heading" level="2" id="hd_id3154123" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="15">Saving $[officename] documents for a mobile device</paragraph>
  <list type="ordered">
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3153192" l10n="U" oldref="16">Choose <emph>File - Save As</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3148672" l10n="U" oldref="17">Open the <emph>File type</emph> box and select the appropriate filter.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3145419" l10n="U" oldref="18">Enter a name and click <emph>Save</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
  </list>
  <paragraph role="heading" level="2" id="hd_id3153768" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="19">Opening mobile device documents in $[officename]</paragraph>
  <list type="ordered">
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3147287" l10n="U" oldref="20">Choose <emph>File - Open</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3147428" l10n="U" oldref="21">Open the <emph>File type</emph> box and select the appropriate filter.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3148618" l10n="U" oldref="22">Select the file and click <emph>Open</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
  </list>
  <paragraph role="heading" level="2" id="hd_id3159196" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="23">Synchronizing file types</paragraph>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3145272" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="24">To convert Pocket PC formats to and from $[officename] formats, you must first change some options within ActiveSync. To do this, open the ActiveSync window and open its Options dialog. Perform the following steps:</paragraph>
  <list type="ordered">
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3149064" l10n="U" oldref="25">Select the <emph>Rules</emph> tab.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3147216" l10n="U" oldref="26">Click the <emph>Conversion Settings</emph> button.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3154145" l10n="U" oldref="27">Click the <emph>Device to Desktop</emph> tab.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="28" role="listitem" id="par_id3159155" l10n="U">Select <emph>Pocket Word Document - Pocket PC</emph> and click <emph>Edit</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="29" role="listitem" id="par_id3154638" l10n="U">In the drop down list of available conversions, select <emph>$[officename] Writer </emph>and click <emph>OK</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="30" role="listitem" id="par_id3149958" l10n="U">Repeat steps 4 and 5 for <emph>Pocket Excel Workbook</emph> selecting <emph>$[officename] Calc</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
  </list>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3148389" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="31">After these steps you can copy documents between $[officename] and your Pocket PC, either by the ActiveSync software or by the Windows Explorer. The filters will be applied to the document files automatically.</paragraph>
